programme.desc: A ruthless crime syndicate, Qi Sha clan, which is controlled by seven chiefs is terrorizing China. The Imperial Court orders Minister Yang to bring them down by sending undercovers to the clan.

programme.title: Hong Kong Rhapsody
programme.desc: Hong Kong Rhapsody is a musical extravaganza full of song and dance. Peter Chen-Ho stars as a playboy magician who changes his ways after he becomes the guardian of a young singer.

programme.title: The Assassin
programme.desc: A female assassin receives a dangerous mission to kill a political leader in eighth-century China.

programme.title: Twinkle Twinkle Little Star
programme.desc: A beautiful but ignorant woman is abducted by aliens but nobody believes her close encounter. While planning a suicide to prove herself, she meets a failed detective who is also planning his suicide.

programme.title: Mad Monkey Kung Fu
programme.desc: A former Monkey Kung Fu master crippled by a ruthless villain is convinced by his young disciple to teach him monkey kung fu, so as to avenge his shame.

programme.title: Les Belles
programme.desc: Linda Lin Dai and Fanny Fan join the dancing troupe of Kao Pao-shu. Linda and Kaos son Peter Chen, manager of the troupe, have misunderstandings and dislike each other.

programme.title: Full Moon Scimitar
programme.desc: Swordsman Peng fought against many swordsmen and won, so he couldnt accept his first defeat and wanted to suicide. The Sect leader gives him the Full Moon Scimitar on the condition that he will never leave the sect.

programme.title: The Purple Shell
programme.desc: Hui Pui-ching is often ill-treated by her husband Fan Pak-nan, a cruel and uncouth man. At a party, Pui-ching meets rich and erudite businessman, Ha Mon-hin and they are mutually attracted.

programme.title: Mercenaries From Hong Kong
programme.desc: A gang of ex-military guys are hired by a mysterious dame who wants them to go into Cambodia and kidnap the assassin who killed her father.

programme.title: Mist Over Dream Lake
programme.desc: Yen Chun directs and stars in a heartwarming drama about a young girl, Chen whose parents send her to a relatives farm for an unforgettable summer.

programme.title: The Brave Archer 3
programme.desc: The third installment of The Brave Archer series brings Guo Jing and Huang Rong closer together as they struggle to find a cure for the Iron Palm Clans deadly blows.

programme.title: Shaolin Abbot
programme.desc: International favorite, David Chiang, stars as the great Chih Shim, the monk who saved the Southern Shaolin Temple. Joining him is Lo Lieh, the Shaws first international star who returns to his famous role of Shaolin renegade Pai Mei. The result is a true martial arts epic.

programme.title: The Mad Monk Strikes Again
programme.desc: The Mad Monk is up against the equally legendary scholar-turned-genie, Lu Tung Pin. The duo create havoc as they vie with each other, be it in mirth, magic, women or weapons!

programme.title: Crippled Avengers
programme.desc: Three men who have been physically disabled by an evil warlord and his physically-disabled son become friends and learn kung fu so that they can seek revenge with help from an elderly martial-arts teacher and his mentally-disabled pupil.

programme.title: Hex After Hex
programme.desc: Beloved cult director Kueh Chih Hung delivers this deranged romantic tragedy centring on muscular demon Lo Meng, whose attempts to possess the soul of his true love backfire.

programme.title: King Gambler
programme.desc: A master gambler loses his memory and is befriended by a street hustler who discovers his supernatural gambling abilities.

programme.title: The Younger Generation
programme.desc: This is a tragic tale about a young girl, played by Ivy Ling Po, who gets married and has five kids. She and her husband later die, forcing one child to be sold into prostitution to feed the other four.

programme.title: Monkey Kung Fu
programme.desc: A disgraced former Kung Fu expert makes a living as a merchant with the help of a hot headed friend. When the men are harassed by gangsters, the merchant decided to teach his friend monkey boxing so they can defend their business.

programme.title: The Warlord
programme.desc: Two young men join a rebel group after the Chinese Revolution of 1911 and become patriotic heroes accidentally. Assisted by a warlords daughter, they successfully help the rebels steal weapons from the warlord.

programme.title: New One-Armed Swordsman
programme.desc: A devious martial arts master targets young, talented swordsmen, and makes a wager that whoever loses should cut off their arm, then surprises them with a secret technique they cannot counter. One of his previous victims have had enough.

programme.title: Gossip Street
programme.desc: Shaw Bros and TVB stars unite for Wang Fengs ensemble epic. Trouble is brewing when a gangster plans to change the Gossip Street residents favourite hangout into a gambling den.

programme.title: The Thunderbolt Fist
programme.desc: Just after the Chinese Revolution, Japanese invaders start to infiltrate Northeast China. In the film, a vicious judo expert Arashi Tani wants to prove that Chinese are the sick people of Asia.

programme.title: Two Con Men
programme.desc: A wonderfully twisted, pseudo-romantic comedy starring Liang Tien and Chang Ying in an age-old competition between rookie con artist versus the ultimate, experienced flimflam man.

programme.title: Magnificent Wanderers
programme.desc: Millionaire Chu Te-Sa (Chiang) invests his considerable wealth into the rebel movement who are intent on usurping the ruling Mongol powers. His goals are impeded by a lack of support though and the supposed allies he has made in the town are merely eager to get their hands on his money. During an attack where these craven comrades flee, Chu befriends three con-artists who relish the chance to show off their fighting skills. The trio subsequently agree to help Chu in his quest to end Mongol rule and hatch a plan to destroy a major munitions dump.

programme.title: The Venus Tear Diamond
programme.desc: Legendary rival jewel thieves Fragrant Night and Nocturnal Earl travel to Japan to steal the famous Venus Tear Diamond.

programme.title: Ghosts Galore
programme.desc: Young Taoist priest Lu and his friend are nearly killed by a female ghost during an exorcism. Luckily, Master Lian saves their lives, so they beseech him to teach them his skills.

programme.title: Men From The Monastery
programme.desc: When the "godfather of the kung-fu film" Chang Cheh decided to tell their stories with Alexander Fu Sheng, Chen Kuan-tai, and Chi Kuan-chun in the roles, it was cause for celebration. This film is one of the most beloved in the directors filmography. Each hero is given his own story, when they all come together in a final, day-long battle with hundreds of troops, the effect is unforgettable.

programme.title: The Dream Of Red Chamber
programme.desc: The fortunes of the wealthy and influential Jia family based in the capital, and their eventual downfall. Adapted from the famous novel by Cao Xueqin.

programme.title: The Imperial Tomb Raiders
programme.desc: The story revolves around a maverick, a band of woman warriors and a group of ruthless bandits. The maverick teams up with the woman warriors to battle the bandits seeking to raid the emperors tomb.

programme.title: Inside The Forbidden City
programme.desc: The tale of two imperial concubines vying for the emperors favor.

programme.title: The Spiritual Boxer
programme.desc: A con artist uses Kung Fu to swindle villagers for money by pretending to be possessed by angry gods. However, when the villagers are later threatened by bandits he must use the same skills for good.

programme.title: The House Of 72 Tenants
programme.desc: The 72 inhabitants of a dilapidated tenement live under the thumb of a heartless landlady and her sleazy husband. The arrival of a defiant new tenant however, changes their fate.

programme.title: Reunion Dinner
programme.desc: Chao Yang and Zi Hong are soon to wed but both have not met the others parents. When a client requests for a livestream of their reunion dinner to promote his products, it set the stage for their parents first meeting. Estranged from his mother, Yang decides to rent a family for the dinner which results in a series of mishaps and hilarity.

programme.title: The White Storm 3: Heaven Or...
programme.desc: An undercover cop who invade a drug cartel led by a notorious Thai drug lord. In classic heroic bloodshed fashion, the two develop a bond of brotherhood.

programme.title: Lonely Eighteen
programme.desc: Set in the 1980s Hong Kong, Elaine and her best friend Ying enter the entertainment industry hoping to change their fates from poverty. Ying soon becomes a popular porn star but Elaine is lost between being her true self and an actress. When show business declines after a decade, their choices lead them to two different paths in life.

programme.title: Twilight Of Warriors: Walled In
programme.desc: Follows troubled youth Chan Lok-kwun as he accidentally enters the Walled City, discovers the order amidst its chaos, and learns important life lessons along the way.

programme.title: Cliff Walkers
programme.desc: This film follows four Communist Party special agents who embark on a secret operation in the Japanese puppet state of Manchukuo in 1932.

programme.title: How To Choose A Royal Bride
programme.desc: The young emperor Kangxi is attempting to select a bride. His mother has arranged for young available women to visit him so that he may choose.

programme.title: Special Couple
programme.desc: Gu disguising as a couple with Jin to secure his stay in London. Everything goes well until Gu falls for his neighbour, Hermione, and Jins parents pay a surprise visit.

programme.title: Once Upon A Time In Hong Kong
programme.desc: A police sergeant teams up with a triad boss to make billions of dollars in bribes. As a lawyer joins his friend in ICAC, the battle between the righteous and the wicked has just begun.

programme.title: My Indian Boyfriend
programme.desc: A love story between a Hong Kong girl and an Indian boy. It encapsulates the conflicts caused by discrimination as well as differences in social-cultural background, lifestyle and family values between the races.

programme.title: An Abandoned Team
programme.desc: An irritable elderly man joins a team rescuing stray dogs. As they work together to save abandoned animals, the groups efforts demonstrate how compassion can change lives for both humans and canines.

programme.title: Legally Declared Dead
programme.desc: Sean visits Tak and Lings home to follow up on a life insurance case and is shocked to see their sons corpse hanging above him. He suspects Tak and Ling of murdering their son to claim the insurance money.

programme.title: My Blue Summer
programme.desc: Zhi has been secretly in love with Nan since she met him once as a child. After graduating high school, Zhi realizes that she and Nan are in the same university, where they get to know each other by chance and become close friends. However, Zhi is still too shy to express her love for Nan. Will this long-term crush finally turn into true love?

programme.title: Death Stranding
programme.desc: To overhaul the underground gambling industry, the police join hands with the gambling association to crack down on illegal casinos. They auction off new casino licenses to regulate the industry, but this results in an upheaval in the gambling world, unveiling the hidden interests and secrets while sparking conflicts between gangs.

programme.title: The Way We Keep Dancing
programme.desc: This sequel of The Way We Dance features the plight of Hong Kongs grassroots performing artists as they fight against the governments plan to gentrify an industrial district where they settled in.

programme.title: Hand Rolled Cigarette
programme.desc: A retired British-Chinese soldier becomes a target in a triad manhunt when he takes in a young South Asian man who carries a bag of stolen drugs.

programme.title: The Infernal Walker
programme.desc: Ting is an undercover police who infiltrates a triad and Tuen is a triad mole being planted into the police force. While Tang is tired of being an undercover cop, Tuen wishes to quit the triad and become a real police. When the triad boss sets a trap to uncover the moles identity, the two must fight for themselves.

programme.title: Detective Vs. Sleuths
programme.desc: Hong Kong is rocked by a series of cold-blooded murders whose victims are runaway suspects of unsolved cases. The group of killers calls themselves “The Chosen Sleuths". Former top detective Lee vows to bring the brutal killers to justice and prove himself to be the real “Chosen Sleuth” instead of a lunatic.

programme.title: Keep Rolling
programme.desc: Directorial debut of Man Lim Chung, who spent 3 years filming this documentary about the life and filmmaking philosophy of Ann Hui, one of Hong Kong’s greatest filmmakers. It traces Hui’s life story and her 40-year career’s ups and downs using film footages, candid conversations with Hui, and interviews with her collaborators, family and friends.

programme.title: City Of Desire
programme.desc: Sandra returns to Macau after having been in Canada for the last twenty years. Her father is ill and the business is being passed on to her, but she is taken aback to discover that the family business is prostitution.

programme.title: Chasing The Dragon
programme.desc: Crippled Ho came to Hong Kong as an illegal immigrant in 1963 and ruthlessly carved an empire from the chaotic underworld of drug dealers and corrupt police that ruled the city under notorious detective Lee Rock.

programme.title: Another Me
programme.desc: One day, Li accidentally discovers that he looks exactly like the prince! While he aims to secure a high ranking position in the palace, the prince wants freedom, so they decide to switch identities.

programme.title: Confinement
programme.desc: Si Ling moves into her dream home after winning an award and hires a confinement nanny. After giving birth to her daughter, inexplicable incidents start happening in the house, threatening both her and her baby.

programme.title: Treasure Hunt
programme.desc: Peggy shoots an ad on a deserted island while some mysterious men with the treasure map are also there to hunt for the hidden Ming Dynasty treasures. However, the map is stolen by Star who lives on the island.

programme.title: Cloudy Mountain
programme.desc: When a decade-long tunnel project is about to complete, an earthquake strikes and leads to a series of subsidence, landslides, and put a town nearby are at stake. Will the authority blow up the tunnel?

programme.title: The Movie Emperor
programme.desc: Actor Lau Wai-Chi has a huge following of devoted followers and is always keeping an eye on his rivals. After accepting to play the lead in a modest indie drama, Lau begins the laborious process of mastering the acting skills for the role.

programme.title: Tales From The Occult
programme.desc: An old school anthology consisting of three short films, Tales from the Occult is the first in a new omnibus series about the hidden horrors that lurk behind the urban landscape of Hong Kong.

programme.title: Customs Frontline
programme.desc: Hong Kong customs officers discover illegal weapons on a cargo ship and trace them back to an international conflict. Elite agents go undercover, uncovering a transnational operation with roots closer to home.

programme.title: Echoes Of The Thunder
programme.desc: Two half-brothers, Nam and Fire, are top racing drivers. In a racing challenge with Japanese driver Kenji, Fire is seriously injured and depressed. So, Nam decides to compete with Kenji in an illegal street car race.

programme.title: Band Four
programme.desc: An aspiring singer of an indie band called Band Four reunites with her estranged guitarist father following the death of her mother. Together, they support each other through their love and passion for music.

programme.title: Bursting Point
programme.desc: The chief inspector in the anti-narcotics unit remains steadfast in his police officer principles, risking all to combat drug-related activities and apprehend traffickers.

programme.title: CGTN Documentary
programme.desc: Launched on Jan. 1, 2011, CGTN Documentary is the only Chinese TV channel to broadcast documentaries in English 24/7. The channel broadcasts over 1,000 episodes of new programs each year, including top quality documentaries such as “A Bite of China”, “Wild Wonders”, and the 100-episode “A History of China”. CGTN Documentary is an ideal platform for people around the world to learn about Chinas past and present, and is dedicated to promoting the best of Chinese documentaries.

programme.title: Ukiyoe Edo-Life
programme.desc: Centuries ago, Tokyo was known as Edo. More than a million people enjoyed life in this small but abundant city. They live on in ukiyo-e woodblock prints. Each episode is a deep dive into a single print, and an exploration of the soul of Old Tokyo. We examine works by artists like Hokusai and Hiroshige not just for their aesthetic and historical value, but for the stories they tell of everyday life. That is how the people of Edo themselves enjoyed this mass-produced medium.
